# Kynexa Bot (@kynexabot)

A Telegram bot that turns short ideas into AI-generated images, with built-in prompt enhancement.

## Features
- `/generate <idea>` — enhances your idea into a detailed prompt and generates an image
- `/enhance <idea>` — shows the enhanced prompt only, without generating an image
- `/help` — lists available commands

Image generation uses [Pollinations.ai](https://pollinations.ai), which is free and requires no API key.

## Local Setup

```bash
git clone https://github.com/yourusername/kynexabot.git
cd kynexabot
python -m venv venv
source venv/bin/activate   # Windows: venv\Scripts\activate
pip install -r requirements.txt
cp .env.example .env       # then add your bot token inside .env
python bot.py
```

Get a token from [@BotFather](https://t.me/BotFather) on Telegram.

## Deploying on Railway

1. Push this repo to GitHub (`.env` is excluded via `.gitignore` — never commit it).
2. Go to [railway.app](https://railway.app) → **New Project** → **Deploy from GitHub repo**.
3. Select your `kynexabot` repository.
4. In the project's **Variables** tab, add:
   - `BOT_TOKEN` = your token from BotFather
5. Railway detects the `Procfile` and runs the bot as a worker process automatically.
6. Check **Deploy Logs** for `Kynexa Bot started polling...` to confirm it's live.

